Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
All laboratory values are within normal limits except for a mildly decreased HbA1c (3.9%), which may suggest recent hypoglycemia or low average glucose levels. Renal, electrolyte, and lipid profiles are unremarkable. No acute laboratory abnormalities detected; clinical correlation for low HbA1c is recommended.
